(define t47 (list "valid-parens" "Write (valid-parens? s) that checks if parentheses [] {} () are balanced, test with \"({[]})\"" (list "#t") "" (list "Convert string to char codes: (string->list s) -> list of integers" "Use a stack: (let loop ((cs chars) (stack ())) ...)" "Char codes: 40=( 41=)  91=[ 93=]  123={ 125=}" "Opening bracket -> push its CODE onto stack for matching later" "Closing bracket -> check if (car stack) matches the corresponding opening code" "e.g., for ) (41): (and (pair? stack) (= (car stack) 40)) means match" "At end, must return (null? stack) — empty stack means balanced" "(display (valid-parens? \"({[]})\"))")))
